      <p><br/>The two blocks shown here are in contact on a frictionless surface.  Suppose that someone comes along and begins 
      pushing on the left side of block 1, causing both blocks to begin to slide to the right. 
      <b>Assuming you will study the system composed of <i>ONLY block 2</i> treated as a single point particle</b>, determine which of the following interactions are internal to the system and which are external.<br/></p>
    
    <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="11">
      
        <conceptgroup concept="">
          <choice location="random" name="earth1" correct="not relevant to this system">

                The gravitational interaction between the earth and block 1.
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="earth1" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="not relevant to this system">
</optioninput>
              <br/>
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="surf1" correct="not relevant to this system">

The contact interaction between the frictionless surface and block 1.

              <optioninput location="random" name="surf1" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="not relevant to this system">
</optioninput>
              <br/>
            
          </choice>
        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="">
          <choice location="random" name="earth2" correct="external">

                The gravitational interaction between the earth and block 2.

              <optioninput location="random" name="earth2" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="external">
</optioninput>
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="surf2" correct="external">

The contact interaction between the frictionless surface and block 2.

              <optioninput location="random" name="surf2" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="external">
</optioninput>

          </choice>
        </conceptgroup>

            <p>
The contact interaction between block 1 and block 2.
</p>
          
          <optioninput location="random" name="bl1bl2" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="external">
</optioninput>

            <p>
The contact interaction between the person pushing the blocks and block 1.
</p>
          
          <optioninput location="random" name="person1" options="('internal','external','not relevant to this system','not a valid interaction')" correct="not relevant to this system">
</optioninput>

            <p>
The contact interaction between the person pushing the blocks and block 2.
</p>
          
